                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d628">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00114A European War 1939/102: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé at Tangier</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Childs</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-11T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 11, 1942—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>215. Your 584, November 10, 10 p.m. War Department requests that you ask Spanish
                    authorities urgently to place strict guard around grounded American planes.
                    Instructions are being sent direct to the Military Attaché with regard to the
                    instruments which the planes carried.</p>
                <p>The Department would appreciate your views as soon as possible as to how far you
                    feel you could go in endeavoring to obtain the release of the crews without
                    raising difficulties or complications with Spanish officials.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
